<item>
            <title>[WFLY-2917] Unhelpful logging related to slave HC failover</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-2917</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In 8.0.0 we introduced the &quot;discovery-options&quot; notion to the HC&apos;s domain-controller config. One expected usage pattern is there will be a master HC and then one or more slaves started with --backup-dc that act as passive failover DC&apos;s. Other slaves will use discovery-options elements to configure all possible masters. If the regular master fails, a backup can be quickly converted to a master with a couple CLI ops.&lt;/p&gt;

